[PROJECT PROFILE: RDNA AI Guard]
[STAGE: Active Hackathon Blueprint Development (AMD Developer Hackathon ACT II)]

[PROJECT SUMMARY]
RDNA AI Guard is a FinSec intelligence platform that pairs an Angular 19+ Signals dashboard with an async Python FastAPI backend to track network exploits and transaction fraud. It runs token-efficient triage locally via Ollama + Gemma 4. Trusted logs pass instantly at zero token cost. Compromised, high-stakes vectors are dispatched to a multi-agent LangGraph system hosted on Fireworks AI's cloud AMD MI300X processors.

[CODEBASE CONSTRAINTS]
1. Monorepo design containing /frontend (Angular) and /backend (FastAPI).
2. UI updates must bypass extensive component re-renders by anchoring stream hooks into Angular Signals.
3. Python layer handles parsing of low-level packet payloads (via Scapy) and orchestrates structured JSON outputs from Gemma 4.
4. Database interaction is async PostgreSQL. 

[EXPECTATIONS]
When writing code snippets, prioritize performance, type safety, asynchronous patterns, and avoid framework or boilerplate compromises. Maintain a clean, high-performance, enterprise-grade architecture.